# World Explorer

An Angular portfolio project that turns an SVG world map into an interactive country explorer. Selecting a country loads a live World Bank profile with region, income level, capital city, and geographic coordinates.

## Why this project is portfolio-ready

- Demonstrates Angular standalone components, routing, dependency injection, and typed services.
- Integrates a third-party public API with loading, empty, and error states.
- Uses a large SVG as an interactive UI surface instead of a basic form-driven app.
- Includes responsive layout, polished visual design, and accessible labels for a stronger first impression.
- Adds focused unit tests around API mapping and component state changes.

## Tech stack

- Angular 17
- TypeScript
- RxJS
- World Bank Countries API
- Inline SVG map interaction

## Getting started

```bash
npm install
npm start